cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing and its application to driving agents. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a language-grounded driving agent using machine learning techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses recurrent layers and gated attention in its hierarchical policy. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper uses the CARLA framework, which includes visual perception and sensor data for driving. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is relevant as the paper deals with the control of a self-driving car, which falls under the domain of robotics.
